import os
import re
import time
import pickle
import warnings
import numpy as np
import torch

from method import NNSolver
import plot_nivel_tanque_new

warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

def pretty_vec(t, precision=3):
    """Converte tensor para string curta e limpa."""
    return np.array2string(
        t.cpu().numpy(),
        precision=precision,
        separator=", ",
        suppress_small=True
    )

data_path = "datasets/dc_wss/dc_wss_dataset_dc5_ex30"
with open(data_path, "rb") as f:
    data = pickle.load(f)

file_name = "04.model_2025-11-23_16-42-59_dc5_samples30_epochs10.pt"
file_path = os.path.join("models", file_name)

m = re.search(r"_samples(\d+)_epochs(\d+)\.pt$", file_name)
samples, epochs = map(int, m.groups())

args = dict(
    probType="dc_wss",
    hiddenSize=200,
    batchSize=16,
    useCompl=False,
    corrMode="full",
    qtySamples=samples,
    epochs=epochs,
    dc=5,
)

model = NNSolver(data, args)
model.load_state_dict(torch.load(file_path, map_location="cpu"))
model.eval()

inputs_data = [
    torch.tensor([[4, 8, 12, 17, 20, 3, 3, 3, 2.5, 2.5]]),  # FONTINHA
    torch.tensor([[1, 8, 12, 18, 21, 0.1, 1, 3, 2.5, 2.5]]),
    torch.tensor([[1, 8, 12, 18, 21, 2, 1, 3, 2.5, 2.5]]),
    torch.tensor([[1, 8, 12, 18, 21, 3, 1, 3, 2.5, 2.5]]),
    torch.tensor([[0.3, 4, 12, 19, 21, 5, 2, 3, 2, 1]]),
    torch.tensor([[0, 2, 3, 4, 17, 1, 1, 1, 1, 2]]),
]

print("\n==================== MODEL EVALUATION SUMMARY ====================")
print(f"Model: {file_name}")
print(f"Training Samples: {samples}")
print(f"Epochs: {epochs}")
print("===================================================================\n")

for idx, x in enumerate(inputs_data, 1):

    print(f"\n--------------------------- TEST CASE #{idx} ---------------------------")

    t0 = time.time()
    with torch.no_grad():
        y = model(x.float())
    elapsed = time.time() - t0

    # Metrics
    cost = float(data.obj_fn(y, args))
    gt = data.gT(y)[0]
    gTL = data.g_TempLog_Original(y)[0]

    # --- Output Summary ---
    print(f"Input (x): {pretty_vec(x)}")
    print(f"Predicted Output (y): {pretty_vec(y)}")

    print(f"\nTank Levels (gT):")
    print(f"  Levels: {pretty_vec(gt[:-1])}")
    print(f"  Final  : {gt[-1]:.3f}")

    print("\nViolations:")
    print(f"  Max gT       : {torch.max(gt).item():.6f}")
    print(f"  Max TempLog  : {torch.max(gTL).item():.6f}")

    print("\nObjective Function:")
    print(f"  Total Cost   :  {cost:.3f}")

    print(f"\nExecution Time: {elapsed:.4f} s")

    # Plot
    plot_nivel_tanque_new.plot_nivel_tanque_new(
        args, y[0], cost, show=True
    )

print("\n======================== END OF ALL TESTS ========================\n")
